at knows how to\nhandle the `title` tag.\n\n```\nparam tag\n\nThe tag name this parser will handle.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "xml_python.Builder.add_parser", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "tag", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "func", "type": {"name": "ParserType", "xref": {"fqname": "ParserType", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Add a parser to this builder.\n\n```\nparam tag\n\nThe name of the tag that this parser knows how to handle.\n\nparam func\n\nThe function which will do the actual parsing.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "xml_python.Builder.add_builder", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "tag", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "builder", "type": {"name": "Builder", "xref": {"fqname": "xml_python.Builder", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Add a sub builder to this builder.\n\nIn the same way that parsers know how to handle a single tag, sub\nbuilders can handle many tags recursively.\n\n```\nparam tag\n\nThe name of the top level tag this sub builder knows how to\nhandle.\n\nparam builder\n\nThe builder to add.\n```\n"]}], "class_variables": [{"name": "xml_python.Builder.maker", "type": {"name": "MakerType", "xref": {"fqname": "MakerType", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "xml_python.Builder.name", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "xml_python.Builder.parsers", "type": {"name": "Dict", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "ParserType", "xref": {"fqname": "ParserType", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "xml_python.Builder.builders", "type": {"name": "Dict", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Builder", "xref": {"fqname": "xml_python.Builder", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["A builder for returning python objects from xml `Element` instances.\n\nGiven a single node and a input object, a builder can transform the input\nobject according to the data found in the provided element.\n\nTo parse a tag, use the {meth}`~Builder.parse_element` method.\n\n```\nivar ~Builder.maker\n\nThe method which will make an initial object for this\nbuilder to work on.\n\nivar ~Builder.name\n\nA name to differentiate a builder when debugging.\n\nivar ~Builder>parsers\n\nA dictionary of parser functions mapped to tag\nnames.\n\nivar ~Builder.builders\n\nA dictionary a sub builders, mapped to tag names.\n```\n"]}], "exports": [{"name": "xml_python.AttribType", "xref": {"fqname": "xml_python.AttribType", "project": null}}, {"name": "xml_python.Builder", "xref": {"fqname": "xml_python.Builder", "project": null}}, {"name": "xml_python.BuilderError", "xref": {"fqname": "xml_python.BuilderError", "project": null}}, {"name": "xml_python.InputObjectType", "xref": {"fqname": "xml_python.InputObjectType", "project": null}}, {"name": "xml_python.MakerType", "xref": {"fqname": "xml_python.MakerType", "project": null}}, {"name": "xml_python.NoneType", "xref": {"fqname": "xml_pyt